<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-14T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-14T05:00:00-05:00" n="456" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9353: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-14T18:00:00+08:00">August 14, 1937—6
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 14—8:38 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>481. Increasingly heavy bombing by Chinese air craft at Shanghai is
                                going on. Their objective is Japanese flagship tied up near Japanese
                                Consulate General. There are urgent pleas that this war vessel
                                proceed to an anchorage down stream as its present situation is
                                bringing bombs short dropped into the area of foreign refuge where a
                                large number have been killed and others, including Americans,
                                wounded. Situation grave. I have asked Embassy, Nanking, to make
                                    representations.<note n="7" xml:id="d456fn7">See telegram No.
                                    485, August 15, 11 a.m., from the Consul General at Shanghai,
                                        <ref target="frus1937v04#pg_255">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p. 255</ref>.</note></p>
                            <p>Repeated to Department and Tokyo.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>